### Describe the issue you're experiencing

In a Livewire Volt functional component, returning something like Excel::download(...) from an action caused generated compiled-view parse errors such as unexpected token "new" or unexpected token "return" in storage/framework/views/livewire/classes/....

Cause: The PHP code itself was valid, but Volt’s functional component compilation produced invalid generated PHP in this case.

Solution: Convert the Volt functional component to a normal Livewire single-file/class-style component and return the download response from a regular component method. Cleanup: Run php artisan view:clear / php artisan optimize:clear afterward.

The problem occurred under Livewire 4, the same Volt component with Livewire 3 worked before.

